🧠 TrueSight AI — Frontend

A modern, responsive frontend for TrueSight AI, a deepfake detection platform that analyzes images, videos, and audio to determine whether content is real or AI-generated.

🚀 Overview

The frontend is built using React + Vite and provides a smooth, interactive interface for users to upload media, view detection results, and manage authentication.

It communicates with a FastAPI backend and displays AI-powered analysis results in real time.

✨ Features
📁 Upload Image, Video, or Audio files
🔍 Real-time Deepfake Detection Results
📊 Confidence Score Visualization (Charts)
🔐 Secure Authentication (Google / OTP / Email)
🎨 Modern UI with animations
📜 Detection History Dashboard
🛠 Tech Stack
React 18 – UI library
Vite – Fast build tool
Tailwind CSS – Styling
Framer Motion – Animations
Recharts – Data visualization
Context API – State management
🔐 Authentication
Google Sign-In
Phone OTP Login
Email & Password Login

Authentication is handled via Firebase on the frontend and connected to backend JWT-based sessions.

📂 Project Structure
src/
│── components/      # Reusable UI components
│── pages/           # Main pages (Home, Dashboard, Auth)
│── context/         # AuthContext (global state)
│── services/        # API calls
│── assets/          # Images & static files
│── App.jsx
│── main.jsx
🔄 How It Works
User uploads media (image/video/audio)
File is sent to backend via API (FormData)
Backend processes file using AI model
Response (REAL/FAKE + confidence) is returned
UI updates dynamically with results
⚙️ Installation & Setup
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/truesight-frontend.git
cd truesight-frontend
2. Install dependencies
npm install
3. Run development server
npm run dev

Frontend will run on:

http://localhost:5173
🌐 Backend Connection

Make sure backend is running on:

http://localhost:8000

Update API base URL if needed in your service files.

📦 Build for Production
npm run build
⚠️ Notes
Ensure Firebase config is properly set up
Backend must be running for detection features
Large files may take time to process
